annotationA: Protein cycle; Putative transcription factor involved in the generation of biological rhythms. Activates cycling transcription of Period (PER) and Timeless (TIM) by binding to the E-box (5'-CACGTG-3') present in their promoters
annotationB: Protein serine/threonine phosphatase activity; protein phosphatase type 2A regulator activity. It is involved in the biological process described with: spindle assembly; determination of adult lifespan; regulation of cell cycle; autophagy; chromosome segregation; signal transduction
